<paragraph base="F3101289" id="IAS23_17" principles="yes"><paranum>17</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 23"/><data name="paranum" value="17"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS23_P0072">An entity shall begin capitalising <xref base="SL138203" href="../glossary/GLOSSARY_borrowingcosts.dita#GLOSSARY_DI0023/GLOSSARY_P0066">borrowing costs<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0023"/></ph></xref> as part of the cost of a <xref base="F3101211" href="IAS23_5.dita#IAS23_5/IAS23_P0020">qualifying asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0311"/></ph></xref> on the commencement date. The commencement date for capitalisation is the date when the entity first meets all of the following conditions: </p><ol base="F3101291" id="IAS23_L0008" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p base="F3101292" id="IAS23_P0073">it incurs expenditures for the asset;</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p base="F3101294" id="IAS23_P0074">it incurs borrowing costs; and</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p base="F3101306" id="IAS23_P0075">it undertakes activities that are necessary to prepare the asset for its intended use or sale.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>